{{doc/start}}
Lua module that renders sortable wikitables of recipes for items, elements, and buildings. Called by [[Template:RecipeTable]], [[Template:RecipeTable Building]], and [[Template:RecipeTable Recipe]].

Tables have columns for Recipe, Inputs, Outputs, Time, and (where applicable) Building. The Building column is suppressed on building pages where it would always contain the same value.

== Data sources ==

{| class="wikitable"
! Module !! Used for
|-
| [[Module:Data/Recipes]] || Recipe inputs, outputs, base craft time, display names
|-
| [[Module:Data/RecipeIndex]] || Maps item/element identifiers to recipe identifiers (by input or output)
|-
| [[Module:Data/BuildingRecipeIndex]] || Maps building identifiers to lists of recipe identifiers
|-
| [[Module:Data/RecipeBuildingNames]] || Maps recipe identifiers to lists of crafting building display names
|-
| [[Module:Data/Items]] || Resolving item display names
|-
| [[Module:Data/Elements]] || Resolving element display names
|-
| [[Module:Data/Buildings]] || Resolving building display names
|}

All data modules are auto-generated by <code>foundry_parser generate-lua</code>. Do not edit them directly.

== Exported functions ==

=== <code>p.main(frame)</code> ===
Renders a recipe table for an item or element. Called by [[Template:RecipeTable]].

{| class="wikitable"
! Argument !! Description !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> / <code>1</code> || Item or element template identifier (e.g. <code>_base_iron_ingot</code>) || Required
|-
| <code>mode</code> || <code>producing</code> (default), <code>consuming</code>, or <code>all</code> || Optional
|}

The Building column is shown; buildings are linked as <code>NAME (Building)</code>.

=== <code>p.building(frame)</code> ===
Renders a recipe table for all recipes craftable in a specific building. Called by [[Template:RecipeTable Building]].

{| class="wikitable"
! Argument !! Description !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> / <code>1</code> || Building template identifier (e.g. <code>_base_assembler_i</code>) || Required
|}

The Building column is suppressed.

=== <code>p.recipe(frame)</code> ===
Renders a single-row table for one recipe by its identifier. Called by [[Template:RecipeTable Recipe]].

{| class="wikitable"
! Argument !! Description !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> / <code>1</code> || Recipe template identifier (e.g. <code>_base_conveyor_i</code>) || Required
|}

The Building column is shown.

== Notes ==
* Craft time is formatted as <code>Xs</code>, <code>Xm Ys</code>, or <code>Xh Ym</code> as appropriate.
* Elemental inputs/outputs are shown with a litre (<code>L</code>) unit suffix.
* Crafting buildings for a recipe are sorted alphabetically.
* Tables use <code>class="wikitable sortable"</code> for column sorting.
* If no recipes match, the function returns an empty string.
{{doc/end}}
